ic 1/f shape, while at higher\nfrequencies its steep spectral slope (-2) is masked by the more energetic\nperpendicular spectrum (slope -5/3).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 28 Mar 2012 10:27:13 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 9 Apr 2012 18:15:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-04"}
